bothering to heal the main tank.<br>b) casts symbol on himself, but doesn't cast resolution on the main tank .. or anyone<br>c) uses complete heal on the (unbuffed) level 48 rogue<br>d) says &quot;time to stop being a battle cleric and heal i guess&quot; after not having done jack the past 10 minutes<br>e) doesn't do anything when the main tank asks for buffs.. any buffs<br>f) in a tough battle, doesn't bother healing the main tank who's down to 2 bubbles and dropping fast, but instead tops himself off (had a bubble missing)<br>g) doesn't wonder why the tank zones at that point with half a bubble of health left and doesn't come back<br>h) and presumably, doesnt' wonder why he's always LFG!!!!<br>i) Not this particular cleric's fault, but in general.... Thinking celestial heal is the be all end all of all healing spells, and casting it on the tank that's down to 1 bubble and has 2.5k hitpoints. TIP: Use celestial healing on a 2k+ tank when the tank's down 2 bubbles at most, it'll not even heal up to full at that point. Otherwise just stick to Complete Heal.<br><br>At that point I left (fled, really).<br><br>That was my cleric yesterday... I'd been warned.. now I know for sure. *sigh*  I'm never EVER grouping with Yonly.. erm I mean that cleric, again.<br><br>What blows my mind is that he's a guildleader... they are all like level 20 and 30, so presumably THEY have never had to actually group with him. Did he come off Ebay or something? How can you get to 51 and be that clueless!  <p><center><img src="http://www.sa.il24.net/~saran/kyrial/kyrialsig.jpg"></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/15/02 10:58:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uisharramoonsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>