naviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1209.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Agreeing on most...</span><hr size=1> All right. I'm a cleric. I tend to be more of a Battle-Cleric than a Sit-on-my-duff cleric.<br><br>While I don't do ANY of those things on this list (ye gods. Top myself off while the tank is low? Heavens forfend! I tend to die myself, because I forgot to check my OWN health...but everyone else survives...IF there's any deaths at all).<br><br>However, I have my own rant about people who insult battle clerics in general.<br><br>Or rather, a comical tale.<br><br>Hunting the Tower of Frozen Shadow, with a full group. At no point had any of our group gone below 1 bubble of health missing...and I wasn't really needing to cast heals. My mana was at full for the majority of the time, as I was the only cleric, and didn't want to waste it for when I did have to heal.<br><br>Now, we've got no warrior for our tank. Our main tank is a ranger (OR pallie. Can't recall) (go figure.)<br><br>We're parading around on the fourth level (Yes, the fun one with all the mazes and drops and mummies and such) and I'm beating on the beasties with my little stick (Journeyman's Walking Stick is nice when you have a wizzie in the group and no chanter. Ruins their resistances).<br><br>My mana is FULL, and nobody's getting hurt much at all. Meaning, if they're unlucky, they're down to half that blue bubble gone. A waste to cast superior heal on, let alone a complete heal.<br><br>Yet the tank is INSISTING I should be sitting on my duff and meditating.<br><br>I keep telling him I have Full Mana. I don't need to med at full mana. And he tells me I will learn. It's not even that I was casting blasts and wasting mana. I'm pounding with the staff.<br><br>While a bad cleric is a horrible thing...a worse thing is being a good cleric and having someone order you to sit on your duff doing nothing when there's no reason to. Someone telling you your job, in fact.<br><br>Just thought I'd share my tale. <p><html><p><align="left"><img src="http://www.byteoart.com/images/darai.jpg"></align></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 545<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/15/02 12:05:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1209.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  :)</span><hr size=1> I have nothing against a battle caster of any sorts.  We got more than a few in the League of Honour.  As long as they keep in mind that the battle part is usually their secondary role.. if the main tank's dropping low, I&quot;d hope for a heal.  If you got full mana (or close to it), by all means PLEASE use your weapon.   But if the warrior-wannabe causes others to die because they'd rather melee than heal, something is wrong.  If I play a shaman, sure, I'll swing the spear occasionally... but I'll also heal and slow and regenerate and haste... melee is what comes after all those responsibilities.<br><br>that's all, she wrote. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.