have myself).  Then he'd do it again.  And again.<br><br>Then he'd get aggro and run around screaming &quot;on me&quot;.  Each of us tried to explain to him how he was getting aggro and why he didn't need to do what he was doing, but he kept doing it.<br><br>He also would cast Greater Healing immediately after Celestial Healing had been announced and cast.  He must not have known how it works, although it was patiently explained to him by the other Cleric.  Maybe he thought his Greater Heal was having a tremendous effect on the warrior's hit points. <p>"These discourses of heterosexuality oppress us in the sense that they prevent us from speaking unless we speak in their terms."<BR>-Monique Wittig, "The Straight Mind"<BR>andersonrob@earthlink.net<BR>http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/index.html<BR>AIM: RWAnderson<BR>ICQ: 43988595<BR>EverQuest: Lasgalen Lothir of Lux Aeternam, Firiona Vie server<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 8/15/02 4:50:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utresjoli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tresjoli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.shadow-striders.com/images/wolfIcon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elven Princess</span><br>  Posts: 313<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/15/02 4:56:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1209.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cpinternet.com/~theduke/MythStuff/ez-tres.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Signs of a bad cleric</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The sad thing is even bad clerics are better healers than good druids.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  I, and many people I know, would argue to the contrary.  We had one particular cleric in our guild who most people preferred not to group with on raids.  As the highest ranking druid I was often placed in his group to cover for his inattentiveness to party member's health.  <br><br>This same cleric, for some inexplicable reason, was always OOM, too, and would go through mod rods like nobody's business.  He claims he wasn't expending his mana by &quot;nuking&quot;. /shrug  I observed that he tended to heal when party members didn't need it, then didn't heal when they did.<br><br>Druids are very underrated as healers.  No, we don't have complete heal, but we (at least those of us who are competent) can do a pretty good job of keeping party members alive.<br> <p><b>Trésjoli Louveteau<BR><i>Femme d’esprit</i></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvalquisssilverpalm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/15/02 5:08:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1209.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Signs of a bad cleric</span><hr size=1> Hard statement to deconstruct.  All clerics, on paper, are better healers that all druids.  Is a bad cleric a better healer than a good druid?  A good druid is absolutely a better <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> groupmate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> than a bad cleric, and I'll take the first any day.  But hey, the point is moot.  Druids aren't primary healers into the late game and I think few folks would dispute this fact.  They can lighten a clerics job considerable with regeneration spells, but that's an entirely different role.  That's minimizing downtime, while it's a cleric's job to keep the tank standing when the world comes crashing down.<br><br>As long as we are on this topic in general, kudos to all the great Paladin healers at higher levels.  I find a greater percentage of Paladins really know their jobs as healers than I would ever imagine.  Maybe it has something to do with the fact that you are a paladin for love of it, or not at all, while many clerics are clerics because they figure it's a profession that will help them be uber.  Well, some clerics, at least.<br><br>On a recent raid we went to clear some of the early Plane of Sky and I was woefully short of clerics.  Had all of one, actually.  But I had a tonne of Paladins!  (That's what happens when you raid with the Fellowship)  Well, a Paladin went into each group.  Two in many cases.  And Leedor, in particular, had the job of watching the SA and the slower.  Why?  Any paladin that will offer to go get his wisdom stuff out of the bank so he can concentrate on healing better is a healer in my books.  Belated Kudos, and just another wrinkle in the discussion.<br><br>Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1209.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1209.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1209.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1209.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0>